1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,560
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,560 --> 00:00:04,660
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,660 --> 00:00:09,680
My name is Catherine and today we're going to be helping you set up an answering machine
我是Catherine，今天我们要帮你设置一个答录机。

4
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:10,680
basically.
基本上是这样。

5
00:00:10,680 --> 00:00:11,680
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:15,920
So somebody's calling you, you can't answer the phone so you leave a message and we're
所以有人打电话给你，你没法接电话，就留个言，我们今天要教你这些。

7
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:17,240
going to teach you all about that today.
没错。

8
00:00:17,240 --> 00:00:18,240
That's right.
没错。

9
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:21,480
So let's take a listen to our dialogue and we'll be back in a moment to figure out just
那我们先听一段对话，一会儿回来再分析。

10
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:29,120
what's going on.
到底是怎么回事。

11
00:00:29,120 --> 00:00:31,280
Can you help me set up my voicemail message?
你能帮我设置语音信箱留言吗？

12
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:36,000
I just got this service and I'm not really sure what I'm supposed to say.
我刚开通这个服务，不太确定该说什么。

13
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Sure.
当然可以。

14
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,880
You just basically got to let the caller know who they called and ask them for their contact
你基本上只需要让来电者知道他们打给了谁，然后请他们留下联系方式。

15
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:42,840
information so you can call them back.
这样你就能回电话给他们。

16
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:43,840
Okay.
好的。

17
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:46,240
So I can say, this is Abby's voicemail.
所以我可以这样说：这是Abby的语音信箱。

18
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:47,600
I will call you later.
我稍后会给你回电话。

19
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:49,520
So leave me your name and number.
所以请留下你的名字和号码。

20
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:52,920
That's more or less the idea, but try something that sounds more friendly.
差不多是这个意思，但试试听起来更友好一些的。

21
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:53,920
Okay.
好的。

22
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:55,460
So how about this?
那这样怎么样？

23
00:00:55,460 --> 00:00:58,000
This is Abby and I'm really happy you called.
我是Abby，很高兴你打来电话。

24
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,720
I promise I will give you a ring as soon as I can.
我保证会尽快给你回电。

25
00:01:00,720 --> 00:01:03,200
So please leave me your name and number.
所以请留下你的名字和号码。

26
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,200
Talk to you soon.
回头聊。

27
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:06,920
A little too friendly, Abby.
有点太友好了，Abby。

28
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:07,920
Just say this.
就这样说吧。

29
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:09,280
Hi, you've reached Abby.
嗨，你已接通Abby的语音信箱。

30
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:12,720
I'm unable to answer your call right now, but if you leave me your name and phone number,
我现在无法接听你的电话，但如果你留下名字和电话号码。

31
00:01:12,720 --> 00:01:14,880
I will get back to you as soon as possible.
我会尽快回复你。

32
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:15,880
Thanks.
谢谢。

33
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:16,960
That's perfect.
完美。

34
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:19,640
Can you say that again and record it for me?
你能再说一遍并帮我录下来吗？

35
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:23,480
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

36
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:28,960
So now let's take a look at some language takeaway.
现在来看看一些语言要点。

37
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:29,960
Language takeaway.
语言要点。

38
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:31,880
All right.
好的。

39
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:37,440
In the first sentence, we are asking someone to help me set up my voicemail message.
在第一句话中，我们请别人帮我设置语音信箱留言。

40
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:40,040
So we got two key words there.
所以这里有两个关键词。

41
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:41,040
That's right.
没错。

42
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,040
So let's break it up.
那我们分解一下。

43
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:44,560
The first one is a phrasal verb, to set up.
第一个是短语动词，to set up。

44
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,560
Okay.
好的。

45
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:50,480
You can set a lot of things up, but just remember that set and up, these are the two words that
你可以设置很多东西，但记住set和up是连在一起的。

46
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:51,480
go together.
这两个词。

47
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,480
In this case, we're setting up voicemail.
在这个例子中，我们在设置语音信箱。

48
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:57,040
It means to establish or to start or to put together.
意思是建立、开始或组装。

49
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:58,360
Yeah, to install.
对，安装。

50
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:02,680
Like for example, you get a new computer and you have to connect all the cables and you
比如，你买了台新电脑，需要连接所有线缆。

51
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,920
have to connect the monitor.
还要连接显示器。

52
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:06,120
So you say, can you help me set up my computer?
所以你说：你能帮我设置电脑吗？

53
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,120
That's right.
没错。

54
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,520
So he always helps me set it up.
所以他总是帮我设置它。

55
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:10,760
So my computer, for example.
比如我的电脑。

56
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:11,760
That's right.
没错。

57
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:15,460
And what we're setting up is our voicemail message.
而我们要设置的是语音信箱留言。

58
00:02:15,460 --> 00:02:17,680
So what exactly is voicemail?
那语音信箱到底是什么？

59
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:19,080
Well you know what mail is.
嗯，你知道邮件是什么。

60
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:21,400
We have email and regular mail.
我们有电子邮件和普通邮件。

61
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:26,040
Voicemail is the kind of message you receive on your phone, your cell phone or your home
语音信箱是你手机上收到的一种消息，手机或座机。

62
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:28,960
phone when you don't answer the phone.
当你不接电话时。

63
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:29,960
That's right.
没错。

64
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:35,100
So basically a way for people to leave you a message even though you can't answer them.
所以基本上是一种让别人给你留言的方式，即使你无法接听。

65
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:36,100
That's right.
没错。

66
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:39,040
So this is something that's, it's not text, it's actually a voice.
所以这不是文字，而是声音。

67
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:42,800
So that's why it's called voicemail and you have to set it up.
所以叫语音信箱，你需要设置它。

68
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,800
Okay.
好的。

69
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,760
So there's, there's no automatic voicemail message.
所以没有自动的语音信箱留言。

70
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:48,600
You actually have to make your own or you can choose one.
你实际上得自己做，或者选一个。

71
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,040
And today we're making our own.
今天我们自己做。

72
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:51,240
That's right.
没错。

73
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:55,680
And so we're explaining that we actually just got this service and we don't really know
所以我们解释我们刚开通这个服务，不太清楚。

74
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:58,800
what we're supposed to say or how to set up our voicemail.
该说什么或怎么设置语音信箱。

75
00:02:58,800 --> 00:02:59,800
That's right.
没错。

76
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:03,160
So voicemail messages are a kind of service.
所以语音信箱留言是一种服务。

77
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:06,200
And now who would offer this kind of service, Marco?
那谁会提供这种服务呢，Marco？

78
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,920
Probably your telephone company.
可能是你的电话公司。

79
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:08,920
That's right.
没错。

80
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:13,040
So a telephone company will offer many different services and these are things that you can
所以电话公司会提供很多不同的服务，这些都是你可以用的。

81
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:15,640
pay extra for and they're useful.
需要额外付费，而且它们很有用。

82
00:03:15,640 --> 00:03:16,840
They can help you in some way.
它们能在某些方面帮助你。

83
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:20,160
So another kind of service is three-way calling.
所以另一种服务是三方通话。

84
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,160
Right.
对。

85
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:22,160
That's right.
没错。

86
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:24,920
So actually we're taking a look at this word service as a noun.
实际上我们正在看“service”这个词作为名词的用法。

87
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:28,600
So we have a service or this service.
所以我们有“a service”或“this service”。

88
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:32,320
So the company offers this service.
所以公司提供这项服务。

89
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:34,640
And well, why are we setting up the voicemail?
那么，我们为什么要设置语音信箱呢？

90
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:40,880
And our friend explains that we just basically doing it to let the caller know who they called.
我们的朋友解释说，我们这样做基本上是为了让来电者知道他们打给了谁。

91
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,880
Okay.
好的。

92
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:46,120
So if I call a number and it says, Hey, leave a message.
所以如果我打一个号码，它说“嘿，留言吧”。

93
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,520
I don't know who I'm leaving a message for.
我不知道我在给谁留言。

94
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:50,800
Did I dial the wrong number?
我是不是拨错号码了？

95
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,800
What do I say?
我该说什么？

96
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:52,800
Do I say my phone number?
我该说我的电话号码吗？

97
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:55,760
So this is basically instructions for what to say.
所以这基本上是关于该说什么的指导。

98
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:56,760
That's right.
没错。

99
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:57,760
And you become the caller.
而你变成了来电者。

100
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:58,760
Right.
对。

101
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:02,680
So whoever is making the call is called the caller.
所以任何打电话的人都被称为“caller”（来电者）。

102
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:08,800
And this is why we are setting up our voicemail to let the caller know who we are calling.
这就是为什么我们要设置语音信箱，让来电者知道他们打给了谁。

103
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:13,920
And of course we have to ask the caller for their contact information.
当然，我们还得请来电者留下他们的联系方式。

104
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:14,920
All right.
好的。

105
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:20,160
Now this is important because it's not just something you have with voicemail messages.
这很重要，因为它不仅仅适用于语音信箱留言。

106
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:22,360
You have contact information for many different things.
你在很多不同的事情上都需要联系方式。

107
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:27,360
For example, your medical care, your school, you have to include contact information.
比如，你的医疗保健、你的学校，你都必须包含联系方式。

108
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:31,520
Now this would be your phone number, your address and or your email.
这包括你的电话号码、地址和/或电子邮件。

109
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:32,520
That's right.
没错。

110
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:38,000
So your contact information is not only useful for in a voicemail message, but for example,
所以你的联系方式不仅在语音信箱留言中有用，例如，

111
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:42,880
in a business meeting or a business lunch, you want to get maybe someone else's contact
在商务会议或商务午餐中，你可能想拿到别人的联系

112
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:44,640
information so you can call them later.
信息，以便以后给他们打电话。

113
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:45,640
That's right.
没错。

114
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:46,860
So don't forget, it's also your name as well.
所以别忘了，也包括你的名字。

115
00:04:46,860 --> 00:04:48,560
So I forgot to mention that.
我忘了提这一点。

116
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,560
That's right.
没错。

117
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:50,920
Contact information must have your name.
联系方式必须包含你的名字。

118
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:51,920
All right.
好的。

119
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:56,120
So that's pretty much all we have for the first part of language takeaway.
这就是语言要点第一部分的全部内容。

120
00:04:56,120 --> 00:05:07,080
Why don't we listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back in a bit with Fluency Builder.
我们不如再听一遍对话，稍后回来继续“流利度训练”。

121
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:09,240
Can you help me set up my voicemail message?
你能帮我设置我的语音信箱留言吗？

122
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:13,960
I just got the service and I'm not really sure what I'm supposed to say.
我刚开通这项服务，不太确定该说什么。

123
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:14,960
Sure.
当然。

124
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:18,880
You just basically got to let the caller know who they called and ask them for their contact
你基本上只需要让来电者知道他们打给了谁，并请他们留下联系

125
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:20,800
information so you can call them back.
信息，这样你就可以回电。

126
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,800
Okay.
好的。

127
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:24,400
So I can say, this is Abby's voicemail.
所以我可以这样说：“这是艾比的语音信箱。”

128
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:25,580
I will call you later.
“我会稍后给你回电。”

129
00:05:25,580 --> 00:05:27,520
So leave me your name and number.
“所以请留下你的名字和号码。”

130
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:30,920
That's more or less the idea, but try something that sounds more friendly.
大致是这个意思，但试试听起来更友好一些的。

131
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:31,920
Okay.
好的。

132
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,440
So how about this?
那这个怎么样？

133
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:35,920
This is Abby and I'm really happy you called.
“我是艾比，很高兴你打来电话。”

134
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:38,680
I promise I will give you a ring as soon as I can.
“我保证会尽快给你回电。”

135
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:41,180
So please leave me your name and number.
“所以请留下你的名字和号码。”

136
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:42,440
Talk to you soon.
“回头聊。”

137
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:44,880
A little too friendly, Abby.
有点太友好了，艾比。

138
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:45,880
Just say this.
就这样说：

139
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:47,280
Hi, you've reached Abby.
“嗨，你已接通艾比的语音信箱。”

140
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:50,680
I'm unable to answer your call right now, but if you leave me your name and phone number,
“我现在无法接听你的电话，但如果你留下你的名字和电话号码，

141
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,680
I will get back to you as soon as possible.
我会尽快回复你。”

142
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,680
Thanks.
“谢谢。”

143
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,680
That's perfect.
这很完美。

144
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:57,840
Can you say that again and record it for me?
你能再说一遍并帮我录下来吗？

145
00:05:57,840 --> 00:06:04,640
All right, here we are in Fluency Builder and the first phrase we've got is, how about
好的，现在我们进入“流利度训练”，第一个短语是“how about

146
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:05,640
this?
this？”（这个怎么样？）

147
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:09,600
So we're saying, we've got an example for you.
所以我们在说，我们给你一个例子。

148
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,600
How about this?
这个怎么样？

149
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,600
That's right.
没错。

150
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,600
Then the example.
然后是例子。

151
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:16,360
So we've talked about how about many times already.
我们已经多次讨论过“how about”的用法。

152
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:22,200
So for example, how about we go to the movies or how not to say how about your weekend because
比如，“how about we go to the movies”（我们去看电影怎么样）或者不要说“how about your weekend”（你的周末怎么样），因为

153
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:23,640
that's completely wrong.
那完全是错的。

154
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:27,360
In this occasion, we're talking about how about this and this is like setting it up
在这个场合，我们在说“how about this”，这就像是为

155
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:28,560
for an example.
一个例子做铺垫。

156
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,560
That's right.
没错。

157
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:33,480
So for another example, we could say, so Marco, I'm trying to figure out how to say hello
所以再举个例子，我们可以说，马可，我在想怎么在接电话时说“你好”，

158
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:36,600
when I answer the phone because I don't like the way I say it now.
因为我不喜欢我现在的说法。

159
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,840
I can say, how about this?
我可以说：“这个怎么样？”

160
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:39,840
Hello?
“你好？”

161
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:40,840
Is that good?
那好吗？

162
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:41,840
No?
不好吗？

163
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:42,840
That's all right.
没关系。

164
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:43,840
That's right.
没错。

165
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:44,840
Hello.
你好。

166
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:45,840
That's too strong.
那太强烈了。

167
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:46,840
Yeah, that's good.
是的，那很好。

168
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:47,840
All right.
好的。

169
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:50,840
So basically I'm setting up an example.
所以基本上我在举一个例子。

170
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,720
I'm saying, okay, keep listening.
我在说，好的，继续听。

171
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,000
I will give you an example.
我会给你一个例子。

172
